t/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa9%2Fa4%2F51146ab144b99fafbcb362db67cd%2Fap24116016419306.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8027x4515+0+418/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa9%2Fa4%2F51146ab144b99fafbcb362db67cd%2Fap24116016419306.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8027x4515+0+418/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa9%2Fa4%2F51146ab144b99fafbcb362db67cd%2Fap24116016419306.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8027x4515+0+418/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa9%2Fa4%2F51146ab144b99fafbcb362db67cd%2Fap24116016419306.jpg" class="img" alt="Duke Energy&amp;#039;s Marshall Steam Station coal power plant operates earlier this year near Mooresville, N.C." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Duke Energy's Marshall Steam Station coal power plant operates earlier this year near Mooresville, N.C.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Chris Carlson/AP                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ol class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A small North Carolina town is suing Duke Energy, alleging it knew about climate change &lt;/strong&gt;for over five decades but &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2024/12/04/nx-s1-5213784/climate-utility-lawsuit"&gt;continued to operate coal and gas power plants&lt;/a&gt; that spewed greenhouse gases.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bitcoin hit $100,000 for the first time yesterday.&lt;/strong&gt; The cryptocurrency's value has more than doubled this year, &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2024/12/04/nx-s1-5202832/bitcoin-rally-100-000-crypto-trump"&gt;largely due to Trump's election win&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A South Florida studio is offering tattoos under sedation. &lt;/strong&gt;The &lt;a href="https://www.wlrn.org/business/2024-12-02/tattoo-sedation-south-florida"&gt;sessions cost tens of thousands of dollars&lt;/a&gt; and allow multiple artists to collaborate on big pieces, cutting down the process time. (via &lt;a href="https://www.wlrn.org/"&gt;WLRN&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This newsletter was edited by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/people/859721331/suzanne-nuyen"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Suzanne Nuyen&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
