at/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd6%2F46%2F1f4f508b4832b3968aecd4a6c12e%2Funtitled-1.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3556x2000+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd6%2F46%2F1f4f508b4832b3968aecd4a6c12e%2Funtitled-1.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3556x2000+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd6%2F46%2F1f4f508b4832b3968aecd4a6c12e%2Funtitled-1.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3556x2000+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd6%2F46%2F1f4f508b4832b3968aecd4a6c12e%2Funtitled-1.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3556x2000+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd6%2F46%2F1f4f508b4832b3968aecd4a6c12e%2Funtitled-1.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3556x2000+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd6%2F46%2F1f4f508b4832b3968aecd4a6c12e%2Funtitled-1.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3556x2000+0+0/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd6%2F46%2F1f4f508b4832b3968aecd4a6c12e%2Funtitled-1.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3556x2000+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd6%2F46%2F1f4f508b4832b3968aecd4a6c12e%2Funtitled-1.jpg" class="img" alt="Left: Halima Ali Adam, A chadian woman lives near Farchana, sits with her baby, Iqbal Abubakr Yaqub, who is 15 months old, at the malnutrition clinic. They&amp;#039;ve been there for 13 days and seen little improvement in the baby&amp;#039;s condition. Right: A person walks through a flooded road after Hurricane Helene hit the area as it passed offshore on September 27, 2024 in Crystal River, Florida. Hurricane Helene made landfall Thursday night in Florida&amp;#039;s Big Bend with winds up to 140 mph and storm surges." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Left: Halima Ali Adam, A chadian woman lives near Farchana, sits with her baby, Iqbal Abubakr Yaqub, who is 15 months old, at the malnutrition clinic. They've been there for 13 days and seen little improvement in the baby's condition. Right: A person walks through a flooded road after Hurricane Helene hit the area as it passed offshore on September 27, 2024 in Crystal River, Florida. Hurricane Helene made landfall Thursday night in Florida's Big Bend with winds up to 140 mph and storm surges.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Claire Harbage/NPR; Joe Raedle/Getty Images                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Giving Tuesday is a global call for generosity inspired by&lt;/strong&gt; Black Friday, Small Business Saturday and Cyber Monday. Thousands of charities are asking for donations. This year, the world's array of disasters has added to the humanitarian needs. If you want to donate to a charity, here's &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/goats-and-soda/2024/10/11/g-s1-27239/giving-tuesday-charity-donations-effectiveness"&gt;how to make sure your donation counts&lt;/a&gt;, according to experts in humanitarian aid. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;💰 &lt;strong&gt;Never give to a brand-new charity without a track record. &lt;/strong&gt;Sources like BBBWise and Charity Navigator can help you check for its track record.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;💰 &lt;strong&gt;You should receive a receipt&lt;/strong&gt; for your donation for tax purposes. If you don't, something is amiss.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;💰 &lt;strong&gt;Giving cash instead of items allows organizations the flexibility &lt;/strong&gt;to support what is needed at all stages of a crisis.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Check out&lt;/strong&gt; the &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/goats-and-soda/2024/10/11/g-s1-27239/giving-tuesday-charity-donations-effectiveness"&gt;full list of guidelines for giving&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;3 things to know before you go&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-36308" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 4032;         --source-height: 2268;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4032x2268+0+378/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2Fde%2F968d483f45edb415bf6b439f5144%2Fap24337548398126.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4032x2268+0+378/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2Fde%2F968d483f45edb415bf6b439f5144%2Fap24337548398126.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4032x2268+0+378/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2Fde%2F968d483f45edb415bf6b439f5144%2Fap24337548398126.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4032x2268+0+378/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2Fde%2F968d483f45edb415bf6b439f5144%2Fap24337548398126.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4032x2268+0+378/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2Fde%2F968d483f45edb415bf6b439f5144%2Fap24337548398126.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4032x2268+0+378/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2Fde%2F968d483f45edb415bf6b439f5144%2Fap24337548398126.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4032x2268+0+378/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2Fde%2F968d483f45edb415bf6b439f5144%2Fap24337548398126.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4032x2268+0+378/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2Fde%2F968d483f45edb415bf6b439f5144%2Fap24337548398126.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4032x2268+0+378/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2Fde%2F968d483f45edb415bf6b439f5144%2Fap24337548398126.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4032x2268+0+378/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2Fde%2F968d483f45edb415bf6b439f5144%2Fap24337548398126.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4032x2268+0+378/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2Fde%2F968d483f45edb415bf6b439f5144%2Fap24337548398126.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4032x2268+0+378/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2Fde%2F968d483f45edb415bf6b439f5144%2Fap24337548398126.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4032x2268+0+378/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2Fde%2F968d483f45edb415bf6b439f5144%2Fap24337548398126.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4032x2268+0+378/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2Fde%2F968d483f45edb415bf6b439f5144%2Fap24337548398126.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4032x2268+0+378/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2Fde%2F968d483f45edb415bf6b439f5144%2Fap24337548398126.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4032x2268+0+378/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2Fde%2F968d483f45edb415bf6b439f5144%2Fap24337548398126.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4032x2268+0+378/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2Fde%2F968d483f45edb415bf6b439f5144%2Fap24337548398126.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4032x2268+0+378/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2Fde%2F968d483f45edb415bf6b439f5144%2Fap24337548398126.jpg" class="img" alt="A snowplow on rounds in Lowville, N.Y., on Monday, Dec. 2, 2024. The region is cleaning up after feet of snow. " loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 A snowplow on rounds in Lowville, N.Y., on Monday, Dec. 2, 2024. The region is cleaning up after feet of snow.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Cara Anna/AP                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ol class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Officials are warning of travel impacts and dangerous conditions&lt;/strong&gt; as &lt;a href="http://www.npr.org/2024/12/01/nx-s1-5211874/lake-effect-snow-northeast-and-midwest"&gt;heavy snowfall continues to bury&lt;/a&gt; portions of the Northeast and upper Midwest this week.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;"Brain rot" is the Oxford University Press's word or phrase of 2024. &lt;/strong&gt;Influential philosopher Henry David Thoreau, born more than 200 years ago, is &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2024/12/02/nx-s1-5213682/writer-thoreau-warned-of-brain-rot-in-1854-now-its-the-oxford-word-of-2024"&gt;credited for the term&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Three years ago, Clarice, who was 14, was admitted to the hospital during a mental crisis.&lt;/strong&gt; After nearly 12 hours of questioning, two EMTs became her unsung heroes because they did not talk to her about what happened but instead &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2024/11/29/g-s1-36232/on-the-darkest-day-of-her-life-two-unsung-heroes-give-clarice-a-moment-of-respite"&gt;provided her with a bit of light&lt;/a&gt; during her ambulance ride.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;       &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This newsletter was edited by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/people/859721331/suzanne-nuyen"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Suzanne Nuyen&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
